  "text": "The API call chain between Grafana and Loki for instant queries operates as follows:\n\n1. **Grafana HTTP Client (grafana/grafana)**: The `LokiAPI` struct in `pkg/tsdb/loki/api.go` (lines 29-34) serves as the primary HTTP client for Loki queries. This struct contains an `*http.Client` and handles all HTTP communication with Loki. The `DataQuery` method (line 161) constructs HTTP requests using the `makeDataRequest` function, which builds requests to the `/loki/api/v1/query` endpoint for instant queries (line 86).\n\n2. **Loki HTTP Handler (grafana/loki)**: The `InstantQueryHandler` function in `pkg/querier/http.go` (lines 122-154) is the server-side function that parses and processes incoming HTTP instant query requests. This function accepts a `queryrange.LokiInstantRequest`, validates that the query is a metric query (not a log query), checks entry limits, and executes the query using the appropriate query engine.\n\n3. **Call Flow**: Grafana's `LokiAPI.DataQuery()` calls `makeDataRequest()` to construct an HTTP GET request to the Loki endpoint `/loki/api/v1/query?query=...&time=...`, which is then sent to Loki's `InstantQueryHandler`, which parses the query parameters and executes the instant query.\n\nSources:\n- [Loki HTTP API Documentation](https://grafana.com/docs/loki/latest/reference/loki-http-api/)\n- [Query examples](https://grafana.com/docs/loki/latest/query/query_examples/)"
}

